<section class="cover-letter" id="cover-letter">
  <div class="wrapper">
    <h2>Intro</h2>

      <article class="cover-letter__content">
        <p>In early 2016 I was contacted by Oliver Tomlinson from information design agency TDL-Creative to help rebuild the TDL website to accomodate for the company's expansion into the West Midlands. Oliver wanted to showcase the two locations, the various team members, the company's extensive client list, &amp; most importantly set up something to help the company transition from TDL-London to TDL-Creative.</p>
        <p>From the outset I knew it was going to be a bigger project than I was used to. The original TDL-London website had a lot of content, despite the fact that it seemed like a one-pager, &amp; Oliver had plans to extend all of that content. The biggest issue with all of that content was how to display it, how to navigate it, &amp; how to tie it all together. How would we explain the different branches? Is all of the work from "one" company or two?</p>
      <p>
        <a href="assets/img/raw/tdl-london-website.jpg" title="Click to see the full website" target="_blank"><img src="assets/img/raw/tdl-london-website_in-post.jpg" alt="The original TDL-London website"></a></br>
        <small>The original TDL-London website design.</small>
      </p>
        <p></p>


      </article>
  </div>
</section>


